section.section:
A school district may develop differentiated compensation programs that provide additional compensation above the single salary schedule described in KRS 157.420 and defined in KRS 157.320. Differentiated compensation plans shall have one (1) or more of the following purposes:
To recruit and retain teachers in critical shortage areas;
To help reduce the number of emergency certified teachers employed in the district;
To provide incentives to recruit and retain highly skilled teachers to serve in difficult assignments and hard-to-fill positions;
To provide career advancement opportunities for classroom teachers who voluntarily wish to participate; or
To reward teachers for increasing their skills, knowledge, and instructional leadership within the district or school.
